Step-by-Step Instructions
Clone the Project

Clone the project repository to your local machine.
Install Dependencies

Navigate to the frontend directory and run:
bash
Copy code
npm install
Navigate to the backend directory and run:
bash
Copy code
npm install
Set Up Environment Variables

In the backend directory, create a .env file.
Add the necessary environment variables as specified in the project documentation.
Start the Frontend

In the frontend directory, run the command:
bash
Copy code
npm run dev
Start the Backend

In the backend directory, run the command:
bash
Copy code
node index.js
Open the Application in Browser

Open your browser and navigate to the application route.
Register Accounts

Go to the registration route and create two accounts:
Account 1 in the first browser tab.
Account 2 in the second browser tab.
Send Friend Request

In the first tab, log in with Account 1 and send a friend request to Account 2 using the username created in the second tab.
Accept Friend Request

In the second tab, log in with Account 2, go to the "Friend Requests" section, and accept the friend request from Account 1.
Start Chatting

Once the friend request is accepted, start a chat between Account 1 and Account 2.